phrases: Interesting.
Wow.
Giggle.
I see.
What are you looking at, Sis?
Just observing.
Do not mind me; continue.
In that case,
I will continue without minding you.
When did you start gaining interest in stuff like that?
You do not need to worry, Sis.
I did not buy these magazines.
I borrowed them.
We have stocked up on postcards with the club's budget, too.
Oh, activities for the Prize Contest Club?
Between a dietary supplement set, an assortment of canned salmon, and a special army knife,
which would you like?
This will not do.
I cannot use her for reference at all.
Reference for?
Not a maid, but a little sister...
I still cannot imagine what I would do.
What are you talking about?!
Little sisters are a mix between soothing and adorable!
A-A mix?
It is a delicious event even for us working at the cafe!
Well then, care to give it a try right now?
You should probably change your hairstyle to something more youthful-looking.
A twintail would probably look best on Misa-chan.
Instead of referring to a customer as Master, you need to use Onii-sama and Onee-sama.
And depending on your character, you can arrange it to be Onii-chan or Nee-san and the list goes on!
Kill me now!
You look better in that than I would imagined!
So, what would you like to call them?
Huh?
You know, the customers!
I am going to be calling them Onii-chan!
B-Bro?
Or something like that.
What are you talking about, Misa-chan?
You are young enough to go as far as to saying Onii-tan!
Onii-tan?!
Onii-tan, could you help me get dressed?
Onii-tan, let us sleep together!
If you are a little sister, you should be doing that!
How old is this little sister?
It is Honoka-chan's specialty after all, which is why she is being so ruthlessly strict.
She is in her enthusiast mode now.
So give it a try!
You are now a little sister who is waiting for her beloved brother to come home!
I wonder what is taking Onii-tan so long...
I-I wonder what is taking Onii-tan so long...
Oh!
I think he is home!
I-I think he is home.
C-Come on, do not we all have something that is not our thing?
This is a little too extreme for me...
You are going to use that as an excuse for not being competent enough for your job?
H-Honoka-chan!
I have been meaning to say this for a while.
I do not mind that you are using your aloofness as a goofy character as your selling point,
but is not it common sense to put some effort into learning if you are being hired to work?
There is her alter ego, Black Honoka!
She is out of my control, now!
You accept it after someone tells you you are fine the way you are, not daring to take a step into this side of the world?
That is sheer folly.
Quit acting so spoiled, brat.
Misa-chan!!
Hang on!
Do not worry about it too much!
If you really cannot do it, we can change your shift.
You can just make up for it by working hard for the next event!
Oh, that reminds me!
Our next event is Maid Sentai Day!
I really wanted to be the pink one, but Honoka-chan insists that she is going to be Pink.
What color would you like to be, Misa-chan?
It does not really matter to me.
You are already done for the day?
YOU-Usui!
Oh!
You are the one who always comes to see Misa-chan!
So your name's Usui-kun!
Oh yeah, maybe you might know!
What color should Misa-chan represent?
Color?
We are going to be having a Sentai event in the future,
so I was wondering what would be best for Misa-chan.
Maid Sentai.
I personally think lilac or sky blue would be best,
but that would overlap with the other girls.
I am thinking of making enameled maid costumes that differ in color!
Then a transparent see-through, please-
Shut up, pervert!
Now, now...
You do not have to decide on it right away.
Could you give yourself some time to think about it?
Little sister, soothing...
Little sister, soothing...
Hey, look at this!
Man, you are really into big breasts!
Confiscated!
What?
Adding a message to Misa-chan in the Maid Exchange Notebook?
That will not work, Ikkun.
Misa-chan does not have anything to do with the Maid Exchange Notebook.
But we do not know till we try!
We do know.
She will not reply back.
Besides, other students might find out after recognizing her handwriting.
She never participates in stuff that could leave evidence behind.
But if it is filled with love...!
What is with you today, Ikkun?
Do you have a plan to catch Misa-chan's interest or something?
For example, if we were to attach an illustration to the message like this...
H-He is good!
What is this about, Ikkun?!
I did not know you could draw stuff like that!
I have been hiding this up until now,
but I am actually a closet otaku.
Ikkun, I...
Oh no, I leaked it!
Well, this is pretty good, so I will forgive you.
I was forgiven!
For what?
But then, what color would this flower be?
F-Flower?
Color?
Why so out of the blue?
Question:
What is the color that will look good on Misa-chan, and at the same time, can express her?
You have ten seconds to answer.
It is got to be red!
Red, a color that represents her passionate air and strength of femininity!
It will also look good on her black hair.
I see.
I think it should be purple!
Purple, a color that has both coolness and sex appeal!
A hint of maturity, perfect!
I see.
I-I vote for black!
Black would look best on that well-knit figure of hers!
Put some lacing on it, and there is nothing more to be asked!
Oh...
Well in that case, I would prefer panties with strawberries on them.
Wait, when did we start talking about underwear?
Hey, check it out!
A special issue on little sisters!
Put it down, man.
Those are magazines Prez confiscated, right?
She will make a fuss.
But take a look!
She looks just like Yukimura's little sister!
Huh?!
What, is it really her?
What the hell?
She is an anime character.
I am telling you, dude!
She looks just like her!
Would not you agree, Yukimura?
P-Perhaps?
Besides, I am not even interested in 2-D.
They all look the same to me.
Yeah?
I can get off on this.
I normally go for 3-D though.
Does your sister wear stuff with frills like these?
Of course not!
But man, it must be nice living with someone so soothing.
You are giving her too much credit.
Oh, no!
The announcement club meeting is about to begin!
Well, I am going to go water the flowers, Yukimura.
Later!
Later!
Yukimura.
Yes?!
H-Hey...
Say...
What do you...
N-Nothing out of the ordinary, I guess...?
Next question, what part of her soothes you?
S-Soothe?
Is she really that similar to this anime character in this magazine?!
Prez?
I-I was just looking for a trend in the confiscated items to-
Oh, it is just you, Usui.
So, what were you looking at?
None of your business.
Siblings?
I have some.
Have I never told you?
I have got an older brother and a little sister.
You have to hear this, Misaki!
Both of Shizuko's siblings wear the same glasses she does!
They may look similar, but they are not the same.
Their faces all look the same, too!
I cannot deny that one.
But the glasses are different though.
You have got an older brother?
Is something the matter?
Huh?
N-No,
well, you see, I do not have any brothers.
Was just wondering what it would be like.
D-Do you two get along well?
My brother and I, you mean?
We are not on bad terms, but we are not particularly on great terms either.
That is because they are all like this!
What is that supposed to mean, exactly?
And what about you, Sakura?
I have got an older sister.
We get along so well!
We go shopping together all the time!
Oh...
So both Shizuko and Sakura are little sisters...
Watching them does soothe me, now that I think about it.
Well, I guess it is not simply because they are little sisters.
I guess the Chief wants to create a place that could give the same kind of soothing feeling.
Misaki?
Why are you staring at us like that?
Nothing... was just thinking about how cute you two are.
W-What happened to you?
Or should I be asking, what are you trying to do to us?
Oh my!
You are going to make me fall in love with you, Misaki!
I ask myself again,
Am I really capable of doing this?
Is this really okay, Ikkun?
Are you really going to draw it?
Yeah.
I brought pens in 24 colors.
Which means...!
Yeah!
Purple!
No, you probably should not draw that.
If you really have to draw it, do not use the color pens!
Draw black laces!
No, come on!
Strawberries!
Take the middle and add a leopard pattern!
What the hell?
Thanks for the wait, masters.
One Moe Moe Omelet Rice, but with a special service added.
TLnote:'Annoying' can be written with the kanji for'Flies of May'
Flies...?
May?
Flies of May?
It always impresses me how hardworking she is.
She was lifting dumbells the other day during her break while reading a textbook.
Anyway, she is definitely reliable and level-headed.
She was also quick on the uptake when learning this job, too.
To be blunt, I hated her at the beginning.
I do not know what happened in her family or whatever, but it pissed me off because she was being treated so well.
But she carries heavy things for us, and more importantly,
If it requires muscle power, just leave it to me!
if a bad master happens to go unpleasant...
Could you let her off the hook please, Master?
And the masters love it!
So I figured she was not all that bad.
Convenient to have her around, too.
Onii-tan?
You are really scheming, Honoka.
-chan?
-san?
Three varieties?
What are you looking at?
Just making an observation.
Was wondering what color you would be.
I told you, just pick whatever!
Anything other than'transparent'.
I guess your mind is filled with'Onii-tan' right now?
Shush.
Do not you have a little sister?
Should not it be easy for you to come up with the right image?
Mine does not say things like'Onii-tan'.
And for starters, I have never heard her beg in a doting voice.
If you cannot do it, why do not you ask them to change your shift?
Just take the day off.
Quit acting so spoiled, brat.
I do not want to let out words like I cannot do it or It is impossible so easily!
And what makes Maid Latte so different from regular cafes...
In any case, it is a place where you can experience a special atmosphere.
I finally realized that the staff are encouraged to create that atmosphere.
That is why I am going to act like a soothing chara-
Then is not that all the more the reason not to overwork yourself?
What?
How did you come up with that?!
I think you are fine the way you are.
If your normal self was my little sister, Prez...
If I were your sister?
I would take pictures of your sleeping face daily and make a photo album,
and I would wonder what angle I should use to take today's picture.
In other words, you are just a creep!
You must be tired after a long day!
Still a hint of awkwardness, but she sounds really natural!
Please sit down!
Would you like something to drink?
Or would you rather eat first?
The conversation is a bit cliched,
but I would say she made the mark!
I will acknowledge the fact that she put effort into becoming a loli little sister type.
She probably could have pulled off the Serious and Tidy little sister type,
but I guess she did not realize that possibility.
S-Something wrong?
I should be asking you that, Misa.
Huh?
You never call me'Onii-tan'.
Being so hyped up all of a sudden is a little creepy.
Oh, I know.
You are probably going to ask me to buy you something.
Or is it that you feel guilty about something?
W-
What are you talking about, Onii-tan?
Misa is always like this-
Could it be that you are trying to make up for the fact that you farted in front of me before?
No, Misa-chan!
You cannot actually get mad at a customer's joke...
Well, it is a pretty tasteless joke.
Y-You are so mean, Onii-tan!
Misa did not fart!
Here is...
Where did you get that water?
I only drink water from the Alps.
Could you go get some?
Come on, stop being so selfish!
Please do not give Misa so much trouble, Onii-tan.
Anyway, what would you like to eat today?
Misa would recommend Omelet Rice.
Onii-tan would like a roasted lobster.
Also, a poele with red wine sauce and foie gras, summer truffles on the side.
Come on, stop being so unreasonable.
I keep asking you not to trouble Misa!
Misa, you should not be acting so spoiled, saying you cannot do this and that.
You also lied and said you did not fart.
I did not, you perverted son of a bitch!
Uh-oh, she finally snapped.
You seem to be in a bad mood today, so I am going to leave.
O-Onii-tan...
Y-You know, I do not mind if you visit again.
Th-This is...!
It cannot be...!
Another little sister type?
It has to be that!
That is right!
Neither the loli type nor the serious and tidy type!
The goofy...
Great work today!
You know, I did not expect her to put in as much effort as she did.
Yeah?
But that is her nature, is not it?
Although I wanted to see more of her cute dere side.
Yeah, same.
We already see enough of her tsun side on a daily basis.
But I guess she will not be able to pull that off during an event.
Because, you know, Misa-chan...
Are not you going to thank me?
Why should I?
It was a success thanks to me, right?
I would hardly consider that a success.
It was an embarrassing display of my lack of ability.
When I am putting everything into acting, I lose the ability to make calm decisions,
causing me to flip out like I did.
So stop trying to act.
You are fine the way you are.
There is no way I can soothe anyone by always acting the way I usually do!
Really?
I think you would make the greatest sister in the world.
S-Shut up, stupid!
Hey, look!
Here comes Usui-senpai!
Good luck!
Can I help you?
Y-Yes...!
I am sorry for calling you out here.
W-Well, there is something I wanted to tell you up front.
The thing is, I have always had feelings for you even before I entered this school...!
Will you go out with me?
That was close...!
Usui-senpai?
I am a high-level otaku who loves maids more than anything.
All of my favorite books have to do with maids, and all the cafes I visit have maids.
Of course, I collect figures as well.
I would play maid games, get excited, say stuff like moe moe,
and even crossdress as a maid myself.
Later.
Get yourself together!
He is testing you!
There is no way he is an otaku!
I do not mind!
If that is really true, I will change myself to suit your tastes, senpai!
But that will not do.
Usui.
The next class is about to begin.
Prez...
Please take off your uniform.
What...
You were going to hold in the pain until the next break with your arm like this?
I am not visibly bleeding or anything.
A strong-minded way of thinking, as expected from you.
Besides, why were you watching that?
Your timing is always so good.
Not like I can help it.
You are always there wherever I go.
It is destiny.
Besides, I am the one who is surprised every time.
Especially when I see you at school.
Most of the time, you are protecting the girls and telling off the guys.
It always makes me wonder what shoujo manga you are the'hero' of.
Well excuse me for not being feminine!
What is wrong with a girl protecting other girls?
Did I ever say there was something wrong with it?
But I did not expect you to put your body on the line to protect a guy, like you just did earlier.
What else could I do?
I could not just sit back and watch.
So even if you end up getting hurt really badly,
you would go and save someone regardless of their gender?
Of course.
I would even go and save you.
I am glad to hear it, Misa-chan.
You are making fun of me, are not you?!
Oh my gosh, Misa-chan!
What happened to your arm?!
Sorry, something happened at school.
Someone made a big a deal out of it and applied too much medicine.
I am surprised you can say that when it was so swollen.
Usui!
Men are not allowed to be in here!
I am going to go work my shift, so hurry up and go home!
Roger.
Well then, Chief, I am going out.
Let me know if it starts hurting again, Misa-chan!
Well then, I will be supporting Misa-chan throughout the day,
so you can rest easy.
If you help her out so bluntly, she will just try to work harder.
So please do not let her realize that you are helping her out.
Moe!
Moe!
Moe!
Oh no!
The flowers of moe!
It must be hard for you, Usui-kun.
Not really.
I am just having fun, so I have never thought of it as a bother.
I guess.
Hardworking Misa-chan is fun to watch, I guess.
Not everyone can put their all into everything they do, even if they try.
Even so, Misa-chan does just that to the point that it makes us worry.
PLACEHOLDER
I will pass you someday!
She is an outstanding girl who can already do just about everything,
but it is hard to look away from her since you can really tell that she is trying to work harder.
It is almost like she is giving you the strength to work harder yourself.
Is not that what makes it fun for you, Usui-kun?
Oh yeah, I thought of a good color for Misa-chan.
Huh?
With the meaning of proceeding with the path she thinks is right, and refusing to let anyone else's color dye hers...
White.
Wow, that is kind of unexpected.
What, you were still here?
I told you to go home already!
Oh, and another reason for my choice is because I would like to dye her with mine.
What are you talking about?
Hey, now you are blushing red.
I cannot stop these flowers of moe!
White Misa-chan is so cool!
Beat me up!
Me too!
Me three!
Roger, Boss.
On second thought, please go a little easy on me.
For me, too.
Gosh!
I still cannot hold back these flowers of moe!
Hey Chief, it would be kind of a waste to only use this costume once for that event, right?
We will have it again someday.
Be sure to look forward to Little Sister Day 2!
Please prepare a transparent see-through uniform next time as well.
There he is again.
Feel free to shut up anytime now.
Oh yeah, are you a little sister too, Chief?
Yup, I have got an older brother.
Chief,
a flamboyantly cute girl is in the store.
Wow, you are right.
Oh, she is here!
You are so cute, Misa-chan.
You keep your mouth shut!
